2026-03-24  Doug Blank <doug.blank@gmail.com>

	* gramps/gen/utils/alive.py, gramps/gen/utils/test/alive_test.py,
	po/POTFILES.skip: Fix ProbablyAlive ignoring fallback when birth
	event has no year When a birth event had a date with only month/day set (year=0),
	is_valid() incorrectly returned True because _calc_sort_value()
	converts year=0 to year=1 via _zero_adjust_ymd(), giving a non-zero
	sortval. This caused birth_date to be set to the useless partial
	date in get_person_bd(), so the fallback loop for
	Baptism/Christening/Stillbirth events was never entered.  Fix: replace is_valid() with get_year_valid() for both the birth
	event check and the birth-fallback loop in get_person_bd().
	get_year_valid() explicitly checks that the year value is non-zero,
	so month/day-only dates are correctly treated as having no valid
	birth year and fallback events are tried instead.  Add tests in gramps/gen/utils/test/alive_test.py covering: - Normal birth with valid year (regression) - No birth event falls back to baptism (regression) - Birth event with month/day only falls back to baptism (the bug) - Birth event with empty date falls back to baptism - Birth event with valid year takes precedence over baptism Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

